In the `policy show|list|delete` commands, additionally to the resource name, we were also forcing the user to specify what kind of resource that name is associated to. E.g. `ockam policy show --resource-type tcp-outlet`.

This PR simplifies those commands so the user only has to pass the resource's name. Whether it's a `resource-type` or a `resource` is done automatically by checking if the passed name can be first converted to a valid `ResourceType`, otherwise it's assumed to be a `ResourceName`. This is also the behavior of the `tuified` behavior, so now the UX is the same in both tty and non-tty cases. 

It also improves the json format to display the policies details properly:

```json
# Before
{
  "resource": {
    "Type": "echoer"
  },
  "action": "handle_message",
  "expression": {
    "Ident": "subject.has_credential"
  }
}

# Now
{
  "resource": "myoutlet",
  "action": "handle_message",
  "expression": "(= subject.c 123)"
}
```
